Caption:
I was Burned out, sad and feeling lonely...

So I took 2 weeks unpaid leave and crossed half a continent to go see my friends and surf on my favourite beach. 

My well-being is the most important.
In this world where the people that are supposed to manage public money and work for the good of all are corrupted to the bone and just try to make you sick from every corner. 

But the human body hold so much technology and beauty. 
The mind has so much potential when used well.
And spirit is unbreakable.

And when you found your people, it all lights up 100 times.

Feeling recharged.
Feeling appreciated.
Feeling loved. 

Thanks my beautiful friends for having me and making me feel soooo welcome. 

Until next time üòò

Well-being from Body, Mind and SPIRIT. Is our biggest asset. 
Not an extra $1000 in your bank account.

What is a Psycho-Spiritual Response to Current World Events? 

‚ÄúRichard Harvey is a psycho-spiritual psychotherapist and spiritual teacher whose work goes beyond the present day conceptual and methodological structures of psychology and spirituality. From a deep sense of caring he is refining an approach to contemporary dilemmas that is arguably the only intelligent way to address the problems of mankind‚Äôs future. I wholeheartedly endorse his work, his marvelous writings, and encourage you to pay close attention to his revolutionary courses and seminars.‚Äù ‚Äì Dr Mukesh Aggarwal, MD, VHCA Herbals, CEO at Ayurveda Consultants

In ‚ÄòA Psycho-Spiritual Response to Current World Events‚Äô Richard Harvey writes: ‚ÄúToday we are facing a number of extraordinary world events. In human history these events may be unprecedented and yet the reactions or perhaps the responses we have to these events are quintessentially human. Caption:
Read caption 
Life is always a tad easier when we do what we love. Obstacles will appear more like interesting challenges than looking like stumbling blocks.

The harsh reality, though, is that we don't always have the option of doing what we love (especially in a clime like ours). Sometimes, we have to do what we don't love because what we love is far out of reach or because what we don't love is the level that leads to what we love.

The best thing to do, if what we love isn't available is to develop a love for what we do. What we do will seem less of a chore or punishment if we put deliberate effort into loving it. If we start loving what we do, the journey to what we love may become faster and smoother.

Caption:
Self-betrayal is an unconscious, automatic trauma response to childhood abandonment and neglect. Healing from it requires self-compassion and self-forgiveness work as your parents‚Äô conditional love for you wasn‚Äôt your fault. It was a byproduct of their own unhealed childhood emotional wounding and the resulting psychological immaturity and lack of self-awareness
.

This dynamic often shows up in adult relationships as pursuing ‚Äúunavailable‚Äù people, pursuing people who are uninterested in you, pursuing people who are bad for you, being stuck in cycles of unrequited love, or trying to ‚Äúfix‚Äù your partners
.

Abandoning yourself will not keep others from abandoning you. Betraying yourself won‚Äôt ‚Äúmake‚Äù people love you. Denying your true needs doesn‚Äôt ‚Äúcreate attraction‚Äù. You need to wake up to your New Truth that, as an adult, now you have the power and awareness to CHOOSE YOURSELF. This looks like practicing self-compassion and focusing on building safe, predictable, nurturing relationships with people who truly care about you
.

Join us on Patreon for more of my teachings and to become a part of our self-reparenting community. Link in bio (patreon.com/acceptandact)
.

Caption:
The dark night of the soul is a period of intense spiritual transformation and inner growth, often characterized by feelings of despair, disillusionment, and existential crisis. It is a necessary process for many individuals on the path to higher consciousness and realisation.

The awakening process involves shifting from a state of unconsciousness to a state of awareness and enlightenment. This can be a gradual or sudden realization of deeper truths about oneself, the universe, and the interconnectedness of all things.

Each inner season, such as the dark night of the soul, is a unique opportunity to confront and transcend the limitations we have placed on ourselves through conditioning, belief systems, and societal norms. By facing our fears, insecurities, and shadow aspects, we can break free from old patterns and conditioning that no longer serve us.

Navigating these inner seasons requires courage, self-awareness, and a willingness to embrace the discomfort and uncertainty that can arise during periods of transformation. It is a journey of self-discovery and self-acceptance, leading to a deeper connection with our true selves and a more expansive perception of reality.

Through this process, we can cultivate a greater sense of inner peace, purpose, and fulfillment, and ultimately experience higher states of living and perceiving. It is a journey that requires dedication, patience, and self-love, but the rewards are profound and transformational.

Caption:
Card of the day from the Divine feminine Oracle, by Megan Wattersonü§çüß°‚ù§Ô∏è
.
Giving is receiving. The energy of the universe is merciful. 
.
Empathy is the most mysterious transaction that the human soul can have, and it‚Äôs as accessible to all of us, but we have to give ourselves to the opportunity to identify, to plunge ourselves in a story, where we see the world from the bottom up or through another‚Äôs eyes or heart. Empathy is mercy‚Äôs twin sister. When we can feel into the reality of someone else‚Äôs suffering, we open up to the possibility of mercy. Mercy means exchange. Mercy is the embodiment of compassion. It can feel easy or even natural to have compassion for people who have never harmed us personally. But mercy is having compassion for someone who has. Mercy requires that we give something of ourselves. Here is where the magic comes in, the law of the universe is merciful. The more we give the more we receive. Giving is the true receiving. When we refuse to release our anger towards someone, we are blocking the flow of the universe within us. We are not harming the person who harmed us by remaining angry. We are keeping ourselves from receiving the love and light that is already ours. ü§çüß°‚ù§Ô∏è

Caption:
We are learning to navigate life in a new way, at soul level. We can‚Äôt think our way to solutions anymore. We can‚Äôt figure things out. We can‚Äôt judge what is happening. We have to navigate through a sudden knowing, by our felt senses, and by following the energy. It is wildly uncomfortable for the ego, who wants to be safe and in control. Who might try to take over, project its own ‚Äòsafer‚Äô plan onto things, or give you other ideas or distractions. It‚Äôs upon you to see it all. To observe it all and be aware and present. To choose the path of the soul and not of the ego.

We are stepping into deeper trust in our own divine plan. A plan that our human knows nothing of. A plan that only our soul knows, and this is why it‚Äôs so important to follow. Because it is why you came here! It‚Äôs the goals that you (your soul) have - what it wants to experience in this lifetime! So you need to uncurl the human ego‚Äôs (inner child) tight grip on the steering wheel. You need to take over with deep faith in the direction that your soul is leading you, with love and compassion for them, but always divine empowerment.

So even in those moments that the ego fear mind worries, rationalizes, fears or goes into self-protection mode - breathe. Tell it you are always safe, and open yourself to divine guidance. You will know the way. Trust your guidance even when it isn‚Äôt what you expected. Because your path will be a magical surprise!

So much love to you on your journey!

All that unhappy, repetitive thinking wasn't there anymore.

Caption:
Written by Ken Wilber
Read by Vikas Adam
Format: MP3
Bitrate: 64 Kbps

With practical teachings and detailed instructions, Ken Wilber introduces Integral Mindfulness, a new way of practicing the widely popular meditation. Integral Mindfulness applies many of the leading-edge insights of Ken Wilber‚Äôs Integral Theory - the first system to combine Eastern teachings on the five stages of awakening with the eight major Western models of human development, thus portraying the complete path of human evolution. In addition to all the benefits to body, mind, and spirit that standard mindfulness meditation confers, practicing Integral Mindfulness promises a more powerful approach to personal transformation and brings within reach the fullest experience of Enlightenment possible.

Beginning with as little as 15 to 30 minutes of daily sessions, the meditator can gradually expand from there by slowly and easily adding significant aspects of the practice. Meditation instructions and step-by-step guided contemplations are given in detail. Listeners learn how to create a graph to track progress and discover natural strengths and potentials. The book also offers recommended readings and resources to facilitate further study

Caption:
I‚Äôve learned that going above and beyond for others who refuse to show up for you leads nowhere good. My time and energy are precious, so I cannot afford to waste them on one-sided relationships anymore, no matter how much history we share or how much I care about the person. 

I used to tolerate lying and cheating, thinking love could conquer all. But the truth is healthy relationships require mutual care, respect, effort, and communication. So now, if trust is broken through deceit or betrayal, I walk away no matter how difficult it is because I deserve faithfulness and honesty, no exceptions, no negotiations. 

Wishy-washy people, hot one day and cold the next, constantly keep you guessing where you stand. I have no place in my life anymore. The emotional rollercoaster is draining and damaging. I should never have to question if someone genuinely wants me in their life regularly. Consistent, committed caring is non-negotiable from here on out.

And if I express clearly that certain behaviors hurt me, but the person refuses to acknowledge responsibility or change, they have to go. Because promises without follow-through mean nothing. I cannot keep making excuses for unremorseful repeat offenses - that‚Äôs enabling more mistreatment. I have learned boundaries are the bedrock of healthy relationships. And my inner peace comes first now, above all else.

Caption:
So many of us are resistant to accepting our humanness.

We seek and seek and seek. Tiring ourselves to the bone.

Wondering, there must be something wrong with me?

Why can‚Äôt I get it right?

Where is this blissful life I was promised?

I must seek more.

I must think more.

I must know more.

The endless and very economically fruitful spiritual ecosystem.

An industry that has become about pretending.

About looking spiritual while our humanness cries out to be seen.

There comes a time we start to discover that there is nothing left to fix.

Nothing left to mend.

Just a life to be lived.

And the mending, the fixing, happens when we let ourselves live it.

With compassion.

With acceptance.

With a deep reverence of our heart‚Äôs truth.

Utopia arrives on its own when we realize that what we have imagined it to be is not what it is.

Peace arrives when we stop trying to make this human experience something other than human.

When we give up the fight, we can finally put down our guard, and see what has been here all along.

__________

Katie Buemann

Caption:
Serenity Now!

‚ÄúThere‚Äôs no value in digging shallow wells in a hundred places. Decide on one place and dig deep. Even if you encounter a rock, use dynamite and keep going down. If you leave that to dig another well, all the first effort is wasted and there is no proof you won‚Äôt hit rock again.‚Äù
~Sri S. Satchidananda, The Yoga Sutras of Pantanjali~

All philosophies and spiritual concepts can lead to an expansion in consciousness; however, consistency is required. It‚Äôs not enough to parrot the words of a teacher, practice or belief system. We must delve deeply into that which ignites the soul. Transformation is demonstrated by how we choose to walk in the world.

When you have created a firm foundation, you‚Äôll discover that it‚Äôs easier to turn into any challenges that arise. Your spirit seeks opportunities to strengthen the gifts you have discovered and it‚Äôs powerful to see them in motion. Be the observer, pay attention to the mechanisms of the ego, and continue to use your tools.

Your life is your practice. Act with integrity, do your best and accept what is. With hindsight and self-reflection, you may discover greater depths and insight regarding your journey and the perfection of your soul.

Caption:
I didn‚Äôt know what a non-negotiable was when I was settling in my relationships w/my family, kids, partner, friends ‚Ä¶everyone.

I was settling & holding onto unconscious anger & feelings of unworthiness that I didn‚Äôt know I was energetically embodying.

A non-negotiable is such an essential part of us being radically honest w/ ourselves & others about what we simply will not give up or modify for anyone.

It‚Äôs part of discerning what we will & will not accept in all areas of our lives.

Do you know what you non-negotiables are? üíó

When we settle, it is subconsciously linked to a feeling of low self worth & a fear of abandonment or rejection.

W/o awareness, I used to embody the energies of feeling unworthy & fearing being abandoned rejected or judged & I would resort to choosing to do what others wanted over choosing what was best for me b/c of fear of losing them.

Knowing my non-negotiables & continuing to re-visit them has made it easier to let go of relationships that are not in alignment w/ my values.

For example, one of my non-negotiables is I don‚Äôt smoke and I prefer not to be in the company of anyone who does.

So, being in a relationship w/ someone who smokes is not something I will entertain.

If I met a man who was in alignment w/me to explore a relationship in every single way possible; let‚Äôs say he had 9/10 of what I wanted in qualities of a partner & he smoked; that would be enough for me to pass on moving forward w/ him.

Non-negotiables put us in the driver seat of our own lives & also show people how we expect to be treated.

This is no judgement on anyone who smokes; simply my preference. 

If you are a woman who is single & open to Dating; knowing what you will not settle for makes dating so much easier when you know your core values & your non-negotiables.

Us women knowing our worth means we won‚Äôt accept less than what we know we want & deserve. 

Knowing your non-negotiables & standing by them is essential to embodying your radiant feminine energy that naturally magnetizes what you do want‚ù§Ô∏è

When you start feeling all the stuff.
When you‚Äôre feeling everyone else‚Äôs stuff.
What does your inner conversation sound like?

Do you get frustrated? With yourself?

Do you have compassion for yourself?
Do you have gratitude for yourself?
And are you gentle and kind with yourself?

I know that you know which way is better.

I also know that‚Äôs it‚Äôs hard sometimes because we would like to just feel ‚ÄòNormal‚Äô.

Just know that all the ‚ÄòNormal‚Äô people are also struggling with their own stuff.

Caption:
I used to throw these lavish birthday parties, you know? The kind that took weeks to plan and a small fortune to pull off. I told myself I loved doing it, but deep down, it was about the applause at the end of the day‚Äîthe nods, the compliments, the 'wow' faces.

It's not just parties, though. Many of us fall into the trap of doing more to feel valued: longer hours at work, the perfect Instagram shot, the seamless persona. 

Society chants a constant refrain: do more, be more.

But here‚Äôs what I‚Äôve learned: the real magic happens when we do less but with more presence. When we stop performing for others and start living for the moments themselves.

‚ú®Ô∏èBreaking the Cycle

üå±Self-Reflection: Ask yourself, "Am I doing this for me or for the approval of others?" Honesty here is crucial.

üå±Value Presence: Start valuing presence over praise. Be in the moment, whether it‚Äôs a simple lunch or a walk in the park.

üå±Set Boundaries:** It‚Äôs okay to say no to things that don‚Äôt add value to your life. Doing less can often mean living more.

Take a moment to honestly assess where you might be performing or acting just for acknowledgment. This isn't about feeling guilty or ashamed‚Äîit's about gaining awareness. Recognizing these patterns is the first step toward genuine self-expression and deeper personal satisfaction. Share your reflections, let‚Äôs explore this awareness together.
 

 #awakening  #meditation  #innerpeace  #spiritualawakening  #innerpeace #externalvalidation

Caption:
OBSTREPEROUS VA LAUNCH GATHERING 

Obstreperous was conceived as a homage to the culture we call our own. With a vision for technical curation and precision, this event mirrors our dedication. Prepare to journey into the realms at the Obstreperous VA Launch Event on June 22nd, 2024, at The Lalit, Bangalore.

Artist Line-up:

- NecroBoro (@necropsycho1111 @alicedrecords x @oroboro.music.official) @sacredsoundrecords 

We are thrilled to welcome the legendary NecroBoro to Bangalore. 

Consisting of Necropsycho from Brazil, the godfather of the scene, and Oroboro from Germany, a new age psycho and pioneer. Having recently set fire to Obstreperous Goa, they now bring their magic to Bangalore.

- Manvantra (@karan_manvantra) @pralayahrecords
The iconic Karan Manvantra, founder of Pralayah Records and the Karacus Marakus Festival, a steadfast supporter of Obstreperous. His energy and vision are immortalized on the VA Album.

- Quadrahedron (@quadrahedron_madmuzik)
Bangalore‚Äôs own sonic alchemist, representing Madmuzik and India‚Äôs underground scene. After international acclaims in Italy and Oman along with a stellar performance at Obstreperous Goa, he‚Äôs back to ignite his home city.

WHERE? - The Lalit, Bangalore üìç
WHEN? - June 22nd, 2024

This event is powered by Axess zone (@axess.zone). Tickets will be available soon through Clubr, MadVibes, Book my Show, Paytm Insider, Idamos Systems, and Axess zone.

Stay tuned for more magical elements leading up to the VA launch. This is just the beginning of a series of electrifying gatherings across cities, uniting bassheads in chaos and harmony.

Caption:
An incredible panel of physicians, authors, tech entrepreneurs and wellness advocates were brought together by the visionary  @kunalsood.io at @unitednations Headquarters in NYC to ‚Äúunlock human potential through AI, neuroscience and consciousness,‚Äù and help bring solutions to  global mental health issues, with the wonderful keynote speaker, Canada‚Äôs @sophiegregoiretrudeau. 

Here are some stats:
- 1 in 9 people struggle with mental health issues on the planet. (I think that‚Äôs low)
- There is 1 therapist to every 200,000 people. 
- Countries dedicate only 2% of their health care budget to mental health.
- People with mental health issues die 10-20 years earlier. 

I was grateful to have a seat at the table to talk about the power of healing in community, enlarging our spiritual connection, and the sacred path of service. 

I shared about how simple mindfulness tools can help people self-regulate and find a place of center within. That we can universally support people to build a toolbox of inner resources with breath, self-hypnosis, sound, meditation that becomes instituted everywhere. All free and available to all. 

It was personally meaningful to talk about us being in a powerful time of awakening on the planet and that old systems are crumbling around us to usher in something better. To voice my concerns about AI in the area of mental health and to lead the room through a Breathwork exercise to quiet busy minds. 

The day we convened on 5/31 was also proclaimed by the Mayor of NYC as Global Mental Health Leadership Day. This is a beginning and the intention of #wethefuture is to lead the way supporting others to thrive mentally and emotionally.

Caption:
üåü I was born in Bogota, Colombia and raised in Rio de Janeiro, Brasil. My father was from CT. I speak English, Spanish, Portuguese, French and Italian. 
üåüWhen I was 4 years old, I had my first experience with death when I witnessed my poodle get hit by a car on Christmas Eve.
üåüWhen I was 3, I broke my right arm; at 12, I broke my collar bone horseback riding. At 17, I had knee surgery (torn ligaments) on both knees at the same time. I was bedridden for 1 month with casts from ankles to hips.
üåüWhen I was 12, I turned down an offer from a pro swim coach (Flamengo) who wanted to be my coach. 
üåüWhen I couldn‚Äôt have a dog, I had a black Rex Rabbit named Amazon.
üåüI love swimming and swam with the dolphins with Joan Ocean in Hawaii.
üåü In Boston 1979, my first job was dog walking for a Saint Bernard named Sulki.
üåüMy first degree was in Simultaneous Translation in 3 languages: French, Spanish & English. I received a Paralegal Certificate from SF State University and worked in biotech & an IP Law Firm in SF.
üåüI went skydiving 2x in Yolo County, CA.
üåüI love to drive and drive a stick shift and have driven cross country from CA to FL 3 times with a rottweiller & a pit bull.
üåü I love using swear words.
üåü I am an HSP.
üåüIn the HD I am a Manifesting Generator 5/1 - Left Angle Cross of Wishes.  Gene Key 3 - Chaos, Innovation, Innocence.
üåüMy mother died in bed with me in 1987.  My father died with 7 brain tumors in 1999 in my house.
üåü When my older brother was sick with Hep C and End Stage Liver Disease, I was his caregiver.
üåü I became a vegetarian in 1984. By 1987 I was juicing. In 2003, was following a Living Foods lifestyle. Today I do not follow a prescribed diet but follow my intuition to know what to eat. 
üåüI practiced Mahayana Buddhism for 30 years and was a guidance counselor in the organization empowering young women.
üåüIn 2007 I had a sensory deprivation / floatation business in San Francisco called Wanna Float?
üåüIn 1999, I studied Vibrational Healing. In 2003, I studied dowsing with Raymon Grace. 2011 I became a Certified BodyTalk practitioner.  2022, I studied with Leonie David - Spiritual Healing.
üåüI only drink Structured Water.
#healing #bodytalk

Caption:
Happy ùêåùê®ùê®ùêß Day Beautiful Soul!

‚ôäIt's Gemini season so shadow work is a must! Deep rapid fire healing flowing through! 
People may be aggressive or angry, ground and tune into you! 

‚ú®While working on your shadow: 
- Center yourself
- Use self compassion
- Reflect for self awareness 
- Be honest and truthful with yourself about your behaviors, attitudes, & dark thoughts. 

‚ú®Taking ownership heals the splits in the mind. 
- Watch your emotional reactions (triggers) 
- Talk to yourself about what you feel and why you feel that way.
- Make a good & bad list so you can see where your beliefs differ. 

‚ú®Choose what you're working on.
Ex. Jealousy
- Face it by accepting and bringing awareness to the feeling. 
- Talk to it by asking 
1. Why are you doing this to me? 
2. What do you want from me? 
3. What are you trying to show me? 
4. What do you have to show me. 
- Always journal!

‚ú®Always remember you have to feel that shit so you can heal that shitüëÅüîÆüßöüèæ!

Caption:
Most empaths don‚Äôt like this about themselves...
¬´hypersensitivity¬ª

This hypersensitivity... can be a source of exhaustion

It can sometimes make the empath feel like an emotional sponge...

Unwillingly absorbing heavy, negative energy that‚Äôs not even theirs!

It makes the evils of the world impossible to ignore.. and the empath feels them in the depth of their bones.
BUT...

This same sensitivity... happens to be EXACTLY what the world needs right now.

Your sensitivity allows you to feel... even from quite a distance... the anguish of another.

Your sensitivity helps you stay rooted in your heart
and compels you to be there for people in need... (anyone)

and I mean TRULY be there...
present...
compassionate...

sincerely ready and willing to help
and that energy my friend...

at least in my opinion is what will change the world.

One warm smile at a time...

One extended arm at a time...

One act of kindness at a time...

If your heart wasn‚Äôt so open, you would probably retreat into your head like most people...

You would probably lose hope and become discouraged at all you‚Äôre seeing in the world...

But your sensitivity doesn‚Äôt allow you to do that!
IT keeps you connected to your heart... your intuition...

that part of you that KNOWS things are gonna end up alright.

Caption:
Authenticity is pretty deep topic.... I explored this word on my own and then asked participants in a Healing Circle to share their thoughts in the chat.

The answers ranged from - someone being dishonest, someone being selfish, someone lying or breaking promises, someone speaking total garbage, and then there came - someone who is not honoring themselves in some way. 

I see truth in ALL these answers. People relate to concepts based on their experiences, introspection, perception, and awareness of human behaviors - flawed and imperfect. 

Now..... my opinion/truth. I look at this a little different... 

There's a "certain level" of truth each of us knows. 
There's a "certain level" of truth each of us recognizes.
There's a "certain level" of truth each of us shares. 

Some people are safe. Some people are not.
Some topics are safe. Some topics are not.

There's a yes/no that's true to form.
There's a yes/no that's a hesitant.
There's a yes/no that's obligation.

There are all types of conversations - conscious and inviting - be-grudging and necessary - annoying and irrelevant. People put on MASKS "to some degree" in order to get along, fit into the mix of people, get along, survive the situation, or manipulate. 

In summary..... I would say there are LEVELS of authenticity (levels of truth) based on our level of integrity and awareness. Also, we must remember that some are more private - revealing more ONLY within their circle. 

Some hold little desire to speak authentically. They may think there's a price to pay for this action. Others may feel that "truth" can be twisted and used as a weapon - as such, standing back from sharing. 

AUTHENTICITY is a valuable skill acquired when we have fine-tuned our capacity to know ourselves, stand our ground, and speak our truth without apology, fear, or concern.

If you'd like to learn more and join our global movement, visit https://bit.ly/3GgFR2N

‚ú®THE EYE OF PROVIDENCE‚ú®

RETROGRADE AWAKENING

God‚Äôs all-seeing eye watching over you in a unique & mysterious necklace. The symbol of the Eye of God is made in a beautiful Labradorite crystal enhanced by the cosmic influence of the moon & star in clear quartz! The Eye of Providence watches over & stimulates your spiritual development, as Labradorite is a powerful spiritual stone. The jewelry is made of divine copper to amplify the crystals energies.

The The Eye of Providence is a powerful symbol believed to represent the watchful presence of a higher power, as well as the idea of ‚Äã‚Äãenlightenment and spiritual awakening. Wearing this pendant can serve as a reminder to seek wisdom and understanding in our lives and to trust the guidance and protection that a higher power provides.

As a symbol, The Eye of Providence has survived for several thousand years. 
The symbol became fashionable in the 17th and 18th centuries as The Eye of Providence of God. The look symbolizes care rather than control. 
From the beginning, God looked out between clouds, then the three sides of the triangle were added, referring to the Father, the Son and the Holy Spirit. But the image is older than Christianity.
It existed in ancient Egypt and has survived in various places, especially around the Mediterranean Sea where it is common to wear eye amulets as protection against the ‚Äúevil eye‚Äù. Not all looks are benevolent.

Caption:
My name is Cecilia Eyvaa Zikara. 

I am a self taught artist and Art has always been the most natural expression to me. 

Life is art and art is life, they are not separate. 

I paint nature, plants, patterns and humans. But they all meet in a dance between the seem and the unseen, a meeting of abstract and figurative in a very dreamy composition. Hence I call my art surrealism.

However Creation shares itself through me in many expressions, and painting is just one of them. I write poetry, books, illustrate, sing and as an intuitive I also psychicly express through private sessions mainly via tarot or the quantum field (morphogenetic). In that way the art continues on into other realms the physical comprehension cannot fathom. This journey is the path less path and the path I have always journeyed, the journey always ends in the present moment and that‚Äôs where I am taken and I go with you in all of my Expressions.

Art has always been with me since as long as I can recall, when I was younger it was a path to process my fantasies and emotions. But as I grew up my Art became a way to communicate Love and Truth.

My longing is to create art that touches your Being and initiates your own alchemical journey.

It is my deep gratitude to share this with you.

Caption:
We are living in a world that is moving at a continually accelerated pace. And it‚Äôs essential for us to intentionally slow down and look around from time to time. How much of your life would you say runs on autopilot?

There are often some deeply ingrained currents running underneath the surface of our lives. When we give ourselves the opportunity to take a pause, look at our motivations, and get curious about what is driving us - this is what leads to awakenings which we may never have had otherwise. 

Taking the pulse of our lives is what helps us see what is working and what is not. And from there we can make the shifts and changes necessary in order to live a more balanced and peaceful life, despite the world spinning around us at this accelerated pace.

Has there been a time in your life that you have slowed down, looked around, and taken inventory of what is going on internally? Tell me about it below!

Caption:
This funny quote from Zig Ziglar makes an important point: just like we need to bathe regularly to stay clean, we also need to refresh our motivation every day to keep going üçÉüíß

Motivation is like a muscle that needs regular exercise to stay strong. If we don't keep it up, we can start to feel lazy and stuck.

Simple things like setting small goals, celebrating our achievements, and staying positive can keep our motivation high. Being around positive people and things like reading inspiring books, listening to uplifting music, or talking with encouraging friends can boost our motivation.

Remember that staying motivated, like staying clean, takes regular effort. By finding ways to motivate ourselves every day, we can keep moving forward and achieve our dreams.

Caption:
Miranda Gerzon, Lic.A, MAOM is an alchemist, acupuncturist, and healing artist. She is the founder and owner of Indigo Acupuncture, specializing in Japanese Style Acupuncture. Since her youth, she has known movement and dance to be powerful healers, potent gateways to blissful liberation, divine connection; and to also be at times very challenging for her. This inner knowing led her to Melissa‚Äôs work in 2012 and to years of deep excavation and exploration into the realm of embodiment. The awe-inspiring power humans have to grow, transform and heal energizes her work as an acupuncturist and as a way of life.

She holds a Master of Acupuncture and Oriental Medicine from The New England School of Acupuncture and a Bachelor of Arts in International Development Social Change from Clark University. She has found that the study and practice of Traditional Chinese Medicine to also be a powerful resource for body awareness, embodiment, and spiritual development.

Miranda is here for the embodied revolution towards a more peaceful and just society. With devotion to staying connected to her aliveness, she strives to be someone who can create space for people to feel truly seen.

Stage hypnotism and the portrayal of hypnosis in the entertainment industry have contributed to many misunderstandings of the true nature of hypnosis. Caption:
Is it hard to Love Unconditionally? Omg, yes! ü´¢üò≥
Because we're human beings ü§î

Sometimes we just cannot understand and accept the injustice we see around (‚Äúhow can they act like this?‚Äú). Or we feel really hurt by someone, reasonably angry and disappointed. Then it is soooo soooo hard to see beyond our bleeding wounds, and still love that person, still see many good things in him/her, and stay open-minded about their perspective why they did what they did üò≥ And not to use ours wounds to fight back by hurting that someone, but to choose stay in the state of love and light. That requires so much wisdom üßê

And it is even harder to love yourself unconditionally! With all your mistakes, challenges and flaws üíñ But if we master it, there's nothing we cannot change in our reality to have the best versions of our lives, and make this world a multiple times better place. That is a mastery, but it is more than possible and completely worth it! ‚ù§Ô∏è

Learn. Evolve. Love. Fail. Try again. Choose bad, then choose right. Feel whatever you feel, accept whatever you see and experience with an open mind and heart. Most of the times it won't be easy. And whenever you get caught by fear - just always get back to Love. Even when it's hard... This is how you train this muscle ‚ù§Ô∏è This is how you tame Unconditional Love more and more into you life. 

üé§ We had a wonderful discussion this morning with my great colleague @peterpaulparkerpage (we already had an inspiring conversation on his podcast before, check that out ‚úÖ) for his Highly Sensitive People Group ‚ô•Ô∏èüòá It was such a pleasure! üé§ 

By the way, unconditional Love is not about feathers üòÖ
Though I chose my earnings before knowing the topic ü§£ This topic is complex, but so needed, and still - we can do all this inner work with ease ‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è

And if you want to change your relationship, change yourself! It's not fair to demand other person to change. If you change your beliefs and actions, another person will just allign to your energy.

There's so much more that we discussed! If interested, just let me know, I will share the video with you ü§ó #highlysensitiveperson #unconditionallove

Caption:
A queen walking in her (true) power 

is a woman walking faithfully in the hands of God.‚ù§Ô∏è‚Äçüî•

She is no greater and no less.

She is no more intelligent or less capable.

She is no more powerful nor is she powerless.

She is no more beautiful nor mediocre.

She is no more exquisite nor is she dull.

She is no more magnificent nor is she lackluster.

She is no more liberated nor is she constricted.

She is devoted.

She is divinity embodied.

She is at ease in the remembrance of the truth 

that God has always been by her side.

She stands for truth,

as her presence naturally rattles 

the masquerade of self-deception.

Deeply devoted,

bowing in reverence to the holiness 

that lays within her

and every being on this planet.

In meeting her sacred heart,

she meets the sacred heart of all she encounters.

A being of radiant love and light.

You can try to ignore her,

but it won‚Äôt last.

To my queens‚Ä¶

I see you

and I feel you‚Ä¶deeply. ‚ô•Ô∏è

Caption:
I remember a time in my life when I was in a relationship where the words sounded perfect, but the actions never matched up. It took me a while to realize that despite all the promises and sweet talk, their lack of effort spoke volumes about their true feelings.

Understanding that genuine interest is shown through consistent actions, not just words, was a hard lesson. I kept hoping things would change, but eventually, I faced the truth: if someone wanted to be with me, they would prioritize me.

Recognizing this was a turning point for me. It taught me to value myself more and not settle for empty promises. Actions always reveal true intentions. If you‚Äôre not seeing the effort, it‚Äôs likely because you‚Äôre not their priority.

This experience taught me to trust what I see, not just hear. It‚Äôs a crucial aspect of maturity‚Äîaccepting that lack of effort clearly shows a lack of interest. By embracing this, I‚Äôve built healthier relationships based on mutual respect and genuine commitment.

Caption:
I‚Äôve had to decide to distance myself from people I cared about deeply. It‚Äôs one thing to decide to cut someone off, but it‚Äôs another to deal with the grief that follows. It‚Äôs a painful process, even when you know it‚Äôs necessary for your well-being.

I remember the first time I had to walk away from a long-term friendship. I didn‚Äôt want to do it, but I realized the relationship was no longer healthy. A deep sense of loss and sadness overshadowed the immediate relief. It felt like mourning a part of my past.

What helped me through it was acknowledging those feelings instead of pushing them away. It‚Äôs okay to feel sad and to grieve the loss of a relationship that once meant a lot to you. Over time, I learned to focus on the positive changes from that difficult choice. I started to see how my emotional health improved and how I could invest more in nurturing and reciprocal relationships.

Standing firm on a decision to cut someone off isn‚Äôt about being heartless; it‚Äôs about prioritizing your mental and emotional health. Allow yourself to feel the grief and use it as a stepping stone to build a more supportive and positive environment.

Caption:
Surrender is not giving up
It‚Äôs giving in to the greatness and power within 
People going through a loss of any kind, often say things like, ‚ÄúI‚Äôm staying positive,‚Äù Or, ‚ÄúI‚Äôm trying not to think about it.‚Äù
Sometimes, that‚Äôs code for, ‚ÄúI‚Äôm not letting myself be sad. I‚Äôm not crying, I‚Äôm not giving space to my grief.‚Äù
Emotions are what they are. Layering ‚Äúpositivity‚Äù on top of grief doesn‚Äôt make the grief go away. It just pushes it further down.
What if, instead of striving for positivity, we looked for courage? 
This might sound like, ‚ÄúI‚Äôm finding my way through this. Some days are harder than others, and sometimes I just need to distract myself, but I‚Äôm finding the strength and the support to really grieve this loss.‚Äù
Choose love - as without love, we would not experience grief. 
Choose courage - as a protection for your vulnerable heart. 
Choose unity with support - then let your soul do its job.
.

Caption:
Quote by Denis Waitley:- "Change the changeable, accept the unchangeable, and remove yourself from the unacceptable."

While reading this quotation today, it occurred to me that I should share a few lines with everyone. Nowadays, we all tend to chase after and waste time on things that are #unchangeable.
....Hoping that external forces won't interfere, and instead, we should aim to change ourselves by grasping the message in the quotation.‚úåÔ∏è‚úåÔ∏è

üíôIn life, we often encounter change, whether we embrace it or not. Learning to adapt to the changeable circumstances is key to growth and success. However, there are aspects of life that are unchangeable, such as the passage of time or certain inherent traits in people we meet. Accepting these realities allows us to focus our energy on what we can control and influence.

Moreover, there are situations and individuals that may be unacceptable or toxic to our well-being. It's essential to recognize these and remove ourselves from such environments or relationships to maintain our mental and emotional health. By prioritizing our own boundaries and self-care, we pave the way for a more fulfilling and balanced life.
